  <body><![CDATA[Mr. P, I feel honor in being able to read your excellent opinions on any occasion, but feel unusually blessed today as I am a rare bird, that of a man both educated and literate (at least in the eyes of some) who had not until this weekend, at the age of 38, read the book. I had not seen the movie -- nor wonder of wonders -- had any details spoilt by a jaded world. I imagine the idea that an adult had not read it was too foreign a concept to be worthy of consideration. I just wanted to thank you for the review, and to add one small tidbit about any sense of heavy-handedness. As a first time reader of the book, despite being familiar with literature before and since, they lost none of the emotional impact I suspect they had upon you and many others on their initial reads. Should those lines you cited will wear a little heavy on my eyes the next time I read the book I shouldn't be shocked, but they hit the first time reader just right, I think. Thanks again!]]></body>
  
